e naming effect in aphasia. These effects persist also through\nageing, in different network representations of younger and older lexicons.\nThis study indicates the need to prevent failure of high multidegree and viable\nwords in the mental lexicon when pursuing the design of effective language\nrestoration strategies against cognitive impairing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jan 2020 16:59:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-15"}
