{"id":"2001.02644","submitter":"Jon  Wolfson","authors":"Jon Wolfson","title":"Uryson Width, Asymptotic Dimension and Ricci Curvature","comments":"The paper uses a modification of the techniques of \"The Fundamental\n  Group of Closed Manifolds with Two-positive Ricci Curvature\". The same error\n  in that paper occurs here. In particular, the proofs of Theorem 2.12 and 2.14\n  contain errors. Therefore Corollary 2.15 is not correct. The limiting\n  procedure does not converge to a geodesic","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A Riemannian n-manifold M has k-dimensional Uryson width bounded by a\nconstant c >0 if there exists a continuous map f from M to an k-dimensional\npolyhedral space P, such that the pullbacks f^{-1}(p) of all points p in P have\ndiameters bounded by c. We prove that an n-dimensional Riemannian manifold M\nwith at least n-k eigenvalues of the Ricci curvature bounded below by a\npositive constant (n-1)b has k-dimensional Uryson width bounded by a constant c\n>0. The constant c depends only on b.\n  In particular, it follows that a Riemannian n-manifold M with scalar\ncurvature S bounded below by a positive constant n (n-1) s has\n(n-1)-dimensional Uryson width bounded by a constant c >0 depending only on s.\nThis result confirms a conjecture of M. Gromov.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jan 2020 17:41:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 May 2020 18:56:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-05"}
